you should have the *option* to change that alignment.. But what if, (like i do) an iksar wanted to be different then the rest of the race... i'm not talking a goody twoshoes or anything, but just neutral or oderly neutral so i could group with my girl.  <br><br>So i guess my main feelings are, alignments are cool... and the way they are implemented is cool.  I just wish that you had the choice of a larger majority of the given alignments...<br><br>Sorry if i bored you all just had to throw that out there... <p>Canth, Iksar Beastlord of Cazic Thule<br>"The blood on my hands is merely proof of my ambition""</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 5:21:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My one probelm with FV and the alignments...</span><hr size=1> I think the purpose behind the alignment restrictions is to really make people think about the RP behind their characters. One dark elven ranger a la Drizzt might be okay. But an army of dark elven rangers and well, you kind of lose the whole &quot;evil sadistic freak&quot; thing that dark elves have going.<br><br>And as for playing something outside of the norm, it's certainly possible...check out all of the IC posts from Sarhea...half elven ranger turned evil by the love of a dark elven samurai. She ended up rerolling as a warrior, it seems, to continue her storyline. Really interesting stuff and much more IC than if she had really continued as a ranger, imho.<br><br>And as for your particular case, high elves can be orderly neutral, so you should still be able to group. I would love to hear the backstory, though, as that is certainly something that would involve a lot of working out, I think, and would likely make a good tale.<br><br>Just my thoughts. <br><br>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uakye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 5:31:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My one probelm with FV and the alignments...</span><hr size=1> thanks this helped alot... i looked up the alignments that high elves can be... and who knows... maybe you'll see a back story sometime soon <p>Canth, Iksar Beastlord of Cazic Thule<br>"The blood on my hands is merely proof of my ambition""</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moandor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 6:52:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: My one probelm with FV and the alignments...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I think the purpose behind the alignment restrictions is to really make people think about the RP behind their characters. One dark elven ranger a la Drizzt might be okay. But an army of dark elven rangers and well, you kind of lose the whole &quot;evil sadistic freak&quot; th